              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two 4x4-in. NaI(T1) scintillators mounted 180",
                " degrees apart, straddled the Ge(Li) detector in order",
                " to clarify and confirm certain lines as double-escape",
                " peaks in the pair-spectrometer mode of the detector",
                " system."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Singles and coincidence gamma-ray techniques.",
                "System calibrated  periodically  with a voltage pulser",
                " to accurately determine energies of the spectral",
                " lines. Carbon ground-state gamma-ray (4945.4 keV) and",
                " 0.511-MeV annihilation radiation peaks, used as",
                " energy standards.",
                "Graphite sample holders used as convenient gamma-ray",
                " energy standards, using the high-energy gamma-ray",
                " transitions at 4945 and 3684 keV from 13C.",
                "Nitrogen contamination purged by flowing He gas through",
                " the reactor tube."
              ]
            }
          ],
